FBIS3-25727 "drafr039_b_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 EAST AFRICA Somalia Aidid Official Condemns Hebron Massacre EA2602191694 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 26 Feb 94 EA2602191694 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the Great Somali People Language: Somali Article Type:BFN [Text] Dr. 'Abd al-Aziz Shaykh Yusuf, the deputy chairman of the Somali National Alliance, SNA, who is also the chairman of the Southern Somali National Movement [SSNM], spoke on behalf of the SNA chairman, the SNA deputy chairman, SNA supporters, and on his own behalf today. He stated that the Somali people had been greatly shocked by monstrous massacre of Muslims praying at the holy Hebron Mosque in occupied Palestine. Dr. 'Abd al-Aziz said the callous act had generated shock throughout the world, particularly the Islamic world. He prayed to god to grant the souls of the departed eternal peace and to provide solace to the bereaved families, the Palestinian people and the Muslims of the world. The SNA deputy chairman appealed to the Somali people to pray for the departed Muslims.
